## ⚙️ Installation

### 1. Clone the repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/Tanishq-Mathur35/fintech-ledger-system.git
cd fintech-ledger-system
```

### 2. Install dependencies

```bash
npm install
```

### 3. Setup environment variables

#### Create a .env file:

```bash
PORT=3000
MONGO_URI=your_mongodb_uri
JWT_SECRET=your_secret_key

EMAIL_USER=your_email
CLIENT_ID=your_google_client_id
CLIENT_SECRET=your_google_secret
REFRESH_TOKEN=your_refresh_token
```

## ▶️ Run the project

```bash
npm run dev
```

### Server runs on:

```bash
http://localhost:3000
```

---

## 🔐 API Endpoints

### Auth Routes

| Method | Endpoint           | Description   |
| ------ | ------------------ | ------------- |
| POST   | /api/auth/register | Register user |
| POST   | /api/auth/login    | Login user    |
| POST   | /api/auth/logout   | Logout user   |

### Account Routes

| Method | Endpoint                  | Description         |
| ------ | ------------------------- | ------------------- |
| POST   | /api/accounts             | Create account      |
| GET    | /api/accounts             | Get user accounts   |
| GET    | /api/accounts/balance/:id | Get account balance |

### Transaction Routes

| Method | Endpoint                               | Description       |
| ------ | -------------------------------------- | ----------------- |
| POST   | /api/transactions                      | Transfer money    |
| POST   | /api/transactions/system/initial-funds | Add initial funds |

---

## ⚠️ Limitations

- No rate limiting implemented
- No input validation library (Joi/Zod)
- No automated tests
- No deployment setup

---

